Hello Andreas,

Thank you for the improvements to the autopkgtest and the other
clean-up.  Using the checksum is a great trick!  One (very minor)
concern I have is that our future selves won't be able to easily
differentiate between a change in the output format in a new version -
for example, capitalization or punctuation or the number of zeros
following the decimal for the XC field in this first line of output:

  >utg000001l LN:i:47676 RC:i:181 XC:f:1.000000

and a legitimately failing test.  I ran into this with a recent update
simrisc.

I don't think we should revert your improvements.  I mention this only
because I see this as an area where we will continue to evolve the state
of the art.

Best regards, and a Happy New Year to all!
tony
